[1] Case updates
- 28 Mar 2019. Epidemiological situation report, DRC Ministry of Health
[in French, machine trans., abridged, edited]
https://us13.campaign-archive.com/?u=89e5755d2cca4840b1af93176&id=76685766e5

The epidemiological situation of the Ebola virus disease dated 27 Mar 2019:
- Since the beginning of the epidemic, the cumulative number of cases is 1044, of which 978 are confirmed and 66 are probable. In total, there have been 652 deaths (586 confirmed and 66 probable) and 325 people recovered.
- 218 suspected cases are under investigation.
- 14 new confirmed cases, including 6 in Katwa, 4 in Vuhovi, 1 in Beni, 1 in Lubero, 1 in Oicha and 1 in Mandima.
- 9 new confirmed cases, including 4 community deaths, including 3 in Vuhovi and 1 in Mandima; 5 deaths at Ebola treatment centers (ETCs), including 4 in Butembo and 1 in Mabalako.
- 1 new probable case validated in Vuhovi whose death occurred on 1 Mar 2019. This is the nurse of a confirmed patient who died on 14 Feb 2019 in Vuhovi.
- 1 new recovered patient discharged from the ETC of Mabalako.
- 2 health workers are among the new confirmed cases in Katwa, all working in the health facility in the Muchanga health area, where several confirmed cases have passed since 10 Mar 2019. The cumulative confirmed and probable cases among the agents is 80 (7.7% of all confirmed and probable cases), including 27 deaths.

News of the response
Beni and Oicha: Reactivation of the epidemic following population mobility
-------------------------------------------------------
- Due to a relatively well-developed road network, the population of North Kivu is very mobile and travels frequently from one health zone to another. This mobility is the main cause of reactivation of the epidemic in health areas where the transmission of the virus had already been stopped.
- This is notably the case of Beni, which had no new confirmed cases between 21 Feb and 20 Mar 2019. Since 20 Mar 2019, the Beni outbreak has been reactivated after a person infected with the Ebola virus from Biakato Mine (Mandima) moved to Beni for treatment. Preliminary investigations revealed that of the 7 new confirmed cases reported in Beni since 20 Mar 2019, 6 are linked to a Biakato Mine transmission line and one was infected after attending the funeral of a confirmed case in Butembo.
- The same is true for the last 2 new cases confirmed in Oicha. These are family members of a confirmed case, a child from Biakato Mine who died in Oicha on 20 Mar 2019.

Vaccination
----------
- Since vaccination began on 8 Aug 2018, 92 502 people have been vaccinated [see URL above for total number of vaccines in each location].

--
